post_text:
U Prep Middle welcomed more than 130 new students over the past two weeks for SummerBridge 2020. And eighteen amazing U Prep teachers, counselors, and ops staff came together to make a new home for them at a distance ‚Äî including Mr. Phillips, who played our mascot, Oscar, at today's end-of-program SteppingUP! awards event.

Mr. Phillips's/Oscar's message was clear: we can't wait to meet you in person ‚Äî and even though we're apart we are not alone.

See you again in 53 days (and don't forget to read Pax and Roller Girl!).

#gatorstrong #apartbutnotalone #knowledgeequalspower

post_text:
One year ago, U Prep Middle opened its doors to its first fifth and sixth graders. From the first day, we've believed that all students should have and keep their own laptops as a resource and a tool ‚Äî to do independent research, to improve their typing, to keep their classes and schedules organized, to communicate with others, and to work collaboratively, even at a distance.

Today we made sure, again, that all our incoming students have what they need to be successful in SummerBridge and beyond ‚Äî wherever we'll be learning.

Resources = Knowledge = Power

Taught by U Prep staff members, SummerUP! gives Gators the opportunity to blog, learn to video-edit, make art, write stories, travel, study graphic novels and more!

Registration is now open, but hurry ‚Äî space is limited to 20 students per camp class.

Click on link in the bio to see all the classes and register.

SummerUP! starts this Monday, July 6!

post_text:
#TeacherTuesday today! Let‚Äôs give #madUPs to Mr. Fajardo!!

From fencing to football, from Ballroom dancing to Badminton, our fleet footed physical education teacher, Mr. Fajardo does it all! Thank you for making sure our students stay active, learn the value of self-care, and appreciate healthy living.

Did you know that in 2019 the Bronx was named the least healthy county in New York for the tenth consecutive year? Many school-age students in our community face health related challenges, including asthma, obesity, and malnutrition which impact their ability to learn and thrive. What Mr. Fajardo does isn‚Äôt just fun, it's saving lives.

As Athletic Director (and Soccer Coach) he supports and organizes our #Gator scholar athletic program. He may be reserved, but we know he has the heart of a cheerleader. #UPTeacherTuesday

#madUPS this #TeacherTuesday to Ms. Fluellen!!

As our MS Operations Lead, Ms. Fluellen is the glue that holds UP Middle together. To say she‚Äôs hardworking would be an understatement. She is among the first to arrive and last to leave the school everyday‚Ä¶(Does she live there?!) Her superpower is definitely multitasking. Not only does she run the day-to-day operations of the school, she is often acting as an ‚Äúhonorary school counselor‚Äù with the students, main point of contact with our parents, and queen of UP school spirit. If that‚Äôs not enough, Ms. Fluellen ALSO coordinates our entire #LatorGator program, she‚Äôs the #Step coach, the #girlsbasketball coach, and the founder of the #MTLP girls program who‚Äôs mission is to foster the development of well-rounded young women of color. #UPteachertuesday
